 <html:p>Fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b:B]]></fr:tex>, we must check that the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="forest://erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link>. For the centre of contraction, we must construct an element of this <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link>; because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">propositional</fr:link> by <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0048.xml" title="Embeddings are propositional" addr="forest://erct/erct-0048" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-0048" /></fr:link>, the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>, so it suffices by the induction principle for <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0028.xml" title="Propositional truncation" addr="forest://erct/erct-0028" type="local">propositional truncation</fr:link> to observe that the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> is <html:em>inhabited</html:em> because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://