          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>A function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is called <html:em><html:strong>surjective</html:strong></html:em> when for any <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\colon  B]]></fr:tex>, the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="Fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002A.xml" title="Inhabitation and existence" addr="forest://erct/erct-002A" type="local">inhabited</fr:link>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
